    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Identify community schools which demonstrate failing water quality tests, pre-intervention, per World Health Organization (“WHO”) standards or are in need of improved, WASH infrastructure or services.\r\n\tInstall internationally certified water purification systems, one in each community school selected, then verify at post-test that water meets or surpasses WHO quality standards\r\n\tUpgrade toilet facilities at schools.\r\n\tInstall, at each site, distinct drinking and hand washing stations that can effectively accommodate the entire volume of students on site\r\n\tImplement a hygiene education program, in each school served, appropriately designed for urban, modern Nepali students\r\n\tPerform monitoring and evaluation of all Splash interventions,\r\n\tIdentify the most vulnerable schools in terms of sanitation functionalities and work on various indicators to make them more functional and child friendly.\r\n\tSAFHA club formation and training.\r\n\tOrientation and training to focal teacher and school management committee."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
